problem.markdown:
>>According to the impossibility theorem, if we want to control for the false positive rate and the false negative rate, which of the following definitions of fairness is unsatisfiable?<<

( ) Demographic parity {{Error rate balance and demographic parity are not mutually exclusive. <a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/1609.05807.pdf">Here is Jon Kleinberg's paper.</a>}}
(x) Predictive parity {{This is an inherent trade-off in fairness.}}
( ) Selection probability {{Selection probability is a metric, not a definition of fairness.}}
( ) Accuracy equity {{Error rate balance and accuracy equity are not mutually exclusive. <a href="https://go.volarisgroup.com/rs/430-MBX-989/images/ProPublica_Commentary_Final_070616.pdf">Here is a paper discussing accuracy equity.</a> }}
